posts.post_title: FS 1894 N142 Duke Cabinet Ed Delahanty
posts.post_content:
Sold.

The colors are actually brighter than they appear in the first scan. As you can see, there are two tape marks on the back along with a small pencil notation on the back right bottom corner. There is also a back crease that runs across the lower left that can only be seen from the back. Visually, this is one of the finest examples that I have seen. LMK if you have any questions.

I have added another image from my scanner using a different setting. The colors on this one on my monitor are more accurate.
Gorgeous Kevin, best of luck in your sale.
That’s much nicer looking than the SGC 40 that just went in REA for over $15,000. That buyer will be kicking himself if he sees this.

Kevin, that is absolutely stunning and a great example of why I've wanted an n142 for a long time!  Can't wait to get my Nash in the mail tomorrow!

DJ
